The paper deals with decision problems and their complexity, which are central topics in theoretical computer science. The use of Integer Linear Programming and parameterized complexity also suggests a focus on algorithms and optimization, which are common themes in sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The mention of scheduling and social choice problems also suggests a possible connection to cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which often deal with decision-making problems in various contexts.
